a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.04210ca0-e731-4005-aaa9-c3d667354512.description=
Deletes the file or directory specified.

Input Parameters\:
source - full path to file/directory to be removed (can be a UNC path)
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host while deleting.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
success - The specified path was successfuly removed.
failure - Unable to remove file/directory.
a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.04c5320a-318f-4068-949b-68766e35af6c.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified key is null. Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Returns\: The value in the specified key. Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.18c0f9da-9667-411a-ae7b-bb591110bebc.prompt=Enter the date (MM/dd/yyyy HH\:mm) \: a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.1c6b0740-5d1f-4842-ae05-0f3b6e300a86.transition.description=The file ${currentFile} has been deleted. a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.28465846-ef7f-4d27-ac35-d378eafd1253.description=
Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The path to check.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success - The operation succeeded.
a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.2b9f4e5c-8f85-4c5d-adf3-1477a489118d.description=
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The directory to check.
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - The number of children.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success - The operation succeeded.

The inputs must be in the format of date/time format of OO Central Server's, which is dependant of Java Locale. You can use flow " Get Current Date and Time" to check upon the default date/time format. For exmaple, If OO Central Server's locale is English, the input date should be in the format of "July 13, 2006 10\:04\:08 AM". Inputs\: d1 - The first date. For example, if the locale is English, the format should be "July 12, 2006 4\:23\:20 PM" d2 - The second date. For example, if the locale is English, the format should be "July 12, 2006 4\:23\:20 PM" threshold -The number of milliseconds around each date that still allows the dates to be considered equal. Responses\: before - if d1 is before d2. equal - if d1 is < d2 + threshold and d1 > d2-threshold. after - if d1 is after d2. failure - Something went wrong. Returns\: the value of d1-d2 in milliseconds. a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.458fe79b-e7b3-417f-b6f7-f833d35d2cb0.transition.description=The file ${currentFile} is not older than the given threshold. a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.4e1c5fa5-171b-4aa3-a502-ce0b7536d173.transition.description=The file ${currentFile} has been deleted. a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.4fc92714-5e75-4392-9958-192c3ddb7e79.description=Check the current date and time, and returns a java DateAndTime formatted string of it. Responses\: success - Date/time retrieved successfully. failure - Date/time could not be retrieved. a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.58aa1bcc-e12e-4689-85dc-1a63a2f567aa.transition.description=The given path is a directory. a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.5e534848-011f-40f1-8dec-185e97d54327.description=
If the input dateFormat is not specified, it converts a date in the format of date/time of OO Central Server's, which is dependant on the Java locale, to a date either in the format of date/time of OO Central Server's or in the format specified in the input outFormat. 

If the input dateFormat is specified, it converts a date in the format in dateFormat to a date either in the format of date/time of OO Central Server's or in the format specified in the input outFormat.

You can use flow "Get Current Date and Time" to check upon the default date/time format.  

For exmaple, if OO Central Server's locale is English, the input dateFormat is empty and the input outFormat is empty, the input date should be in the format of "July 13, 2006 10\:04\:08 AM". If the user specifies dateFormat as "dd-MM-YYYY HH\:mm\:ss", the input date should be in the format of "13-07-2006 10\:04\:08". If the input outFormat is empty, the result will be "July 13, 2006 10\:04\:08 AM". If the input outFormat is "yyyy-MM-dd", the result will be "2006-07-13".


Specify the date format with the following patterns\:

Letter 	Date or Time Component 	Presentation 	Examples
G 	Era designator 	Text 	AD
y 	Year 	Year 	1996; 96
M 	Month in year 	Month 	July; Jul; 07
w 	Week in year 	Number 	27
W 	Week in month 	Number 	2
D 	Day in year 	Number 	189
d 	Day in month 	Number 	10
F 	Day of week in month 	Number 	2
E 	Day in week 	Text 	Tuesday; Tue
a 	Am/pm marker 	Text 	PM
H 	Hour in day (0-23) 	Number 	0
k 	Hour in day (1-24) 	Number 	24
K 	Hour in am/pm (0-11) 	Number 	0
h 	Hour in am/pm (1-12) 	Number 	12
m 	Minute in hour 	Number 	30
s 	Second in minute 	Number 	55
S 	Millisecond 	Number 	978
z 	Time zone 	General time zone 	Pacific Standard Time; PST; GMT-08\:00
Z 	Time zone 	RFC 822 time zone 	-0800

So, for example\: the date "2006-07-10 15\:16\:14.766 PDT" would have the dateFormat "yyyy-MM-dd HH\:mm\:ss.SSS z".

You can also use single quotes (') to avoid text interpretation. The quoted text will simply be copied into the output string during formatting (if present in the outFormat) or matched against the input string during parsing (if present in the dateFormat). For example, the date value "2006-07-10T15\:16\:14.766Z" would have the dateFormat "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH\:mm\:ss.SSS'Z'". 


Inputs\:
date - The date to parse. If the input dateFormat is empty, the date must be in the format of date/time of OO Central Server's, which is dependant on the Java locale. If the input dateFormat is not empty, the date must be in the format specified in the input dateFormat.
dateFormat - The format of the input date. 
outFormat - The format of the output date/time. If it is empty, the output date/time will be in the format of date/time of OO Cental Server's, which is dependant on the Java locale.
outLocaleLang - The locale language for output string. For example,  en or ja.
outLocaleCountry - The locale country for output string. For example, US or JP. 

Responses\:
success - The date was converted.
failure - The date could not be converted.

Result\:
The date in the new format.

If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. a53ed832-c6d8-4752-bd62-38d6e9eaaca4.830d2e66-4b76-43cf-a511-55594db8469f.description=
Compares a files last modified date/time to a given threshold.

Input Parameters\:
source - The file to read
threshold - The threshold to compare the file modified time to (MM/dd/YYYY h\:mm\:ss a format  Feb 6, 2007 3\:06\:33 PM).
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The file probably could not be found.
greater than	- The file's modified time is larger than the threshold.
less than - The file's modified time is smaller than the threshold.
equal to - The file's modified time is the same as the threshold.

Extra Results\:
date - The file's modified time.

Deletes files with specified extension in the local machine, with an optional date input.

Inputs \:
directory		- Path of the folder in which the delete operation has to be performed.
extension		- Extension of the files that have to be deleted.
time		- The date before which the files have to be deleted. (optional, required in format MM-dd-yyyy HH\:mm).
user		- User credentials of the system in which the delete operation has to be performed (optional).
password		- Password of the user login (optional).

Responses \:
success		- Delete operation performed successfully.
failure		- Error occurred while executing  the flow.

Gets a list of one or more Elements in a list that match a given filter.

Inputs\:
list - the list to search.
delimiter - The delimiter that separates elements in list.
compareTo - The string to compare each element in the list against.
matchType - The type of match to perform.

Responses\:
success - 1 or more elements were found that matched.
failure - no elements matched, or something went wrong.

Returns\:
A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.

Results\:
others - all elements that did not match
matches - A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.
